What you need to know:

The High Court upheld a decision by an arbitrator compelling the company to settle the lump sum and accrued interest.The tribunal further ordered the water firm to pay accrued interest at 12 per cent per annum on the award from November 2018 and arbitrator's fees among other payments.Meanwhile, National Water Conservation and Pipeline Corporation has been ordered to pay a law firm more than Sh40 million for services rendered.